<div>
<h2>Once you settled in for your Move, things to remember</h2>
<div class="row car-transport">
<div class="col-sm-4 car"><img src="https://www.grewaltransportservice.com/img/Combine-2.webp" alt="Moving To A New State" class="car-img" width="100%" height="350"></div>
<div class="col-sm-8 car-body">
    <p>Check that all of your items arrived securely once you arrive at your destination. Check the inventory or list you made when you were packing for any damaged or missing items. The transport and logistics will also have a sheet with a list of everything they loaded into the van and its original condition.</p>
    <p>If everything appears to be in order and matches the inventory sheet, ask the representative to provide you a copy of the document. If the moving company leaves before you discover any damage, take pictures of the damaged objects for proof and to file a claim. Complete the unpacking. You'll have a fantastic sensation when you break down your last box.</p>
    <h3>Update your driver’s license and vehicle registration</h3>
    <p>Updating your driver's licence and vehicle registration with the Motor Vehicle Agency might be a major pain if we don't follow the laws and regulations. On their website, you may learn about the procedure of getting a new licence or changing your address in your licence. Your vehicle's registration must also be updated. Also, double-check that your car insurance is valid in your new state.</p>
